@vrothberg For portability better use the generic shebang? I also hat problems with `-x` and `-e` in the past, since it throw me out of a _screen_ session...

```
#!/usr/bin/env bash
# fetch and checkout a github pull request
# Usage: checkoutpr $remote $PR-ID (e.g., checkoutpr upstream 007)
git fetch -f -u $1 pull/$2/head:pull-request-$2 && git checkout pull-request-$2
```

or wrap it into a function:
```
checkoutpr() { git fetch -f -u $1 pull/$2/head:pull-request-$2 && git checkout pull-request-$2 }
```

